<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 18 at 3:40PM EDT  by NWS Louisville</headline>
<description>...Patchy Frost Possible Late Tonight...
Low temperatures tonight into Tuesday morning will bottom out near
freezing. If winds diminish enough, some patchy frost and perhaps
a light freeze will be possible in typically cold spots, such as
sheltered valleys in rural areas.
Stay up to date on the latest forecasts, and cover vegetation that
may be sensitive to temperatures near freezing.</description>
